This paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and specifically on discourse structure, which is a key aspect of NLP. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses learning latent representations, which is a common topic in machine learning, particularly in deep learning. This suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on various tasks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions modifications to the proposed model, which could involve neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category.
